FBIS4-31912 "dreeu116__a94039" FBIS-EEU-94-116-A Daily Report 14 Jun 1994 ANNEX Yugoslavia, Kosovo Serbs `Maltreat' Albanians Crossing Border Serbs `Maltreat' Albanians Crossing Border AU1406183694 Tirana ATA in English 1024 GMT 14 Jun 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU1406183694 Tirana ATA English BFN [Text] Tirana, June 14 (ATA) -- People have to wait in long queues up to seven hours to cross the border points between Kosova and Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] in Han Elezi and Gllobocica. Serbian forces in this border crossing point exercise a severe and detailed control, maltreat and provoke Albanians, get their passports under various pretexts, especially as a punishment for visits to Albania. After being deprived of their passports, the Albanians are sent to jail or punished by very high fines.
